NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Now as to how to play a nine card trump fit. In general, missing the Queen you play for the drop as opposed to finessing for the Queen. But missing the King with a 9 card fit, you still take the finesse. Because the odds of a singleton King offside are pretty small, whereas the odds of the club finesse working are 50%. With the Queen, it turns out the odds of either a 2-2 break or the Queen being singleton are slightly greater than 50%. That is why with a 9 card fit you play for the drop of the Queen. But the King is a totally different matter.|
