^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|If one person has shown a long suit, even a 5 card major, I play the other person for the Queen. My thinking is, because the person with the long suit has fewer cards outside their suit than her partner. Her partner is more likely to have the Queen. For example on this hand, say Roberta  was missing the club Queen instead of the club King. In that case, since Patti showed a six card suit, I would have finessed Dee for the Queen of clubs.|
