^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|By the way, Dee Dee wanted to know about the sandwich NT. If one opponent opens and the partner responds (for example 1D-P-1S), if you play the "sandwich NT", a 1N overcall by you after 1S shows the other 2 suits--sandwich NT. It differs from a takeout double as It tends to show a weaker hand and it tends to show better minor holdings than major suit holdings. Depending on distribution, can be 8 or 9 HCP if you are 5-4 with a singleton. |
